            "heading": {
                "type": "heading",
                "content": "Start",
                "level": 1
            },
            "items": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<p>Welcome back!</p>\n<p>Today we will focus on life and culture.</p>\n<p>You will practise the following items:</p>\n<p><strong>Have fun!</strong></p>\n"
                }
            ],
            "sections": []
        },
        {
            "reference": {
                "value": "1392388"
            },
            "heading": {
                "type": "heading",
                "content": "Life and Culture",
                "level": 1
            },
            "items": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<img src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361906/ET8G_intro2.png\" class=\"float-right\"/>\n<p>What do you know about England, the English language, English people and other English speaking countries?<br/>\n<br/>\nYou are going to learn more about them in 'Life and culture'!<br/>\n<br/>\nIn this theme you will look at tourism in the UK and other English speaking countries.<br/>\nYou are also going to listen to a song about cultural differences.<br/>\n<br/>\nGet started!</p>\n"
                }
            ],
            "sections": [
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1392391"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "UK geography (1)",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361907/ET8G_intro7.png\" class=\"float-right\"/></p>\n<p><strong>UK Cities</strong><br/>\nDo you know some of the biggest UK cities?<br/>\nBrainstorm with a classmate and try to think of as many UK cities as you know.<br/>\nAny idea where these cities are in the UK?<br/>\nLook them up in an atlas or on the internet.<br/>\nYou should now be ready for the 'Cities of the UK quiz'.<br/>\n<br/>\nGo to the website of <a href=\"http://lizardpoint.com/geography/uk-cities-quiz.php\">Lizardpoint</a> and practise with the geography of UK cities.</p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1392393"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "UK geography (2)",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361906/ET8G_intro2.png\" class=\"float-right\"/></p>\n<p><strong>Quiz your classmates!</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Work with a partner.</li>\n<li>You choose a city from on of the cities you have seen on page 1.</li>\n<li>Use <a href=\"http://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"underline\"><strong>simple.wikipedia.org</strong></span></a> and write down three facts about this city.</li>\n<li>Give the sheet of paper with facts to another pair.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Do they know what city the facts are about?</p>\n<div>\n<hr/>\nPossible variety:<br/>\nThe 'fact sheets' go round the whole class.<br/>\nEach pair writes down the correct cities on a separate sheet of paper<br/>\n(make sure the fact sheets are numbered).<br/>\nWhen all pairs have written all cities for all fact sheets, the teacher will quiz<br/>\nthe class.</div>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1392398"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "Travelling in English",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361909/ET8G_intro4.png\" class=\"float-right\"/></p>\n<p><strong>Travelling in English</strong><br/>\nOf course, English is not only spoken in England.<br/>\nThat is why it is important you learn more about other countries that have English as an official language too. In this section you are going to prepare<br/>\na presentation on travelling and holidays in an English speaking country other than England.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Choose a classmate to work with.</li>\n<li>Have a look at a list and map of English speaking countries here at <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/English_speaking_countries\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"underline\"><strong>en.wikipedia.org</strong></span></a> . Choose an English speaking country you want to travel to. Make sure you do not have the same country as another group in your class.</li>\n<li>Prepare a presentation on tourism in your English speaking country.<br/>\nCheck the website of <a href=\"http://www.lonelyplanet.com/\">lonely planet</a> for instance for inspiration (how to organise information, what to say).</li>\n<li>The presentation should be in between 1:30 and 2 minutes.<br/>\nMake sure both you and your partner present.</li>\n<li>Finally, vote for the most popular English speaking holiday country in your class.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1392400"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "Englishman in New York",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361910/ET8G_intro3.png\" class=\"float-right\"/></p>\n<p><strong>Englishman in New York</strong><br/>\nHave you ever been to Belgium?<br/>\nDo you think it is very different from the Netherlands?<br/>\n<br/>\nIn Belgium and the Netherlands, we understand each other because we (partially) speak the same language, but our cultures are very different.<br/>\nThe same happens with an Englishman in New York.<br/>\nYou are going to listen to <em>Englishman in New York</em> by Sting now.</p>\n<p>Try to fill in the gaps while you are listening.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<div>\n<hr/></div>\n<p> </p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "reference": {
                "value": "1392402"
            },
            "heading": {
                "type": "heading",
                "content": "Tasks",
                "level": 1
            },
            "items": [],
            "sections": [
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1392403"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "Introduction",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<img src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361912/ET9H_intro2.png\" class=\"float-right\"/>\n<p>In this part you will find a language task that combines the different things you have learned during this theme.<br/>\n<br/>\nHow much do you remember about everything you have learned in this theme?<br/>\nYou will find out here!</p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1392405"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "Planning a trip (1)",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<img src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361913/ET9H_intro4.png\" class=\"float-right\"/>\n<p>Planning a trip on a budget<br/>\nSituation<br/>\nAfter having read about tourism in England in this theme, you and a classmate have become interested in spending your holidays there!<br/>\nOne little problem, your jobs in Albert Heijn have not made you rich yet...<br/>\nYou need to travel on a budget!<br/>\nEach of you has \u20ac500 to spend.<br/>\n<br/>\nWebsites that could help you:<br/>\n<br/>\n<a href=\"http://www.visitbritain.tv\" target=\"blank\"><span class=\"underline c1\">www.visitbritain.tv</span></a><br/>\n<a href=\"http://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/\" target=\"blank\"><span class=\"underline c1\">www.tripadvisor.co.uk</span></a><br/>\n<a href=\"http://www.lonelyplanet.com/england\" target=\"blank\"><span class=\"underline c1\">www.lonelyplanet.com/england</span></a></p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                },
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1392407"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "Planning a trip (2)",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<img src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361914/ET9H_intro5.png\" class=\"float-right\"/>\n<p>Task</p>\n<ul class=\"noindent\">\n<li>You plan a trip to England and make a collage about it.</li>\n<li>You decide how long for and where to but remember you only have \u20ac500 to spend for your whole holiday (i.e. travel, accommodation, food, museums etc.).</li>\n<li>Make sure the following 'decisions' are visible on your collage:\n<ul class=\"noindent\">\n<li>how long you stay</li>\n<li>means of transport</li>\n<li>accommodation</li>\n<li>where you stay (picture of hotel, B and B, etc.)</li>\n<li>what you are going to do</li>\n<li>what you will eat and drink</li>\n<li>prices of everything</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There are many more good websites out there, have a look for yourself!<br/>\n<br/>\nGood luck!</p>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "reference": {
                "value": "1392387"
            },
            "heading": {
                "type": "heading",
                "content": "Words",
                "level": 1
            },
            "items": [],
            "sections": [
                {
                    "reference": {
                        "value": "1392389"
                    },
                    "heading": {
                        "type": "heading",
                        "content": "Introduction",
                        "level": 2
                    },
                    "items": [
                        {
                            "type": "paragraph",
                            "content": "<img src=\"https://maken.wikiwijs.nl/bestanden/361894/ET8D_intro2.png\" class=\"float-right\"/>\n<p>On this page you will find some links to useful other vocabulary exercises about holidays and travel.</p>\n<ul class=\"noindent\">\n<li><a href=\"http://www.learning-english-online.net/areas/vocabulary/private-life/travel-and-tourism/\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"underline c1\">Travel and tourism.</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.myenglishpages.com/site_php_files/vocabulary-lesson-travel.php\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"underline c1\">General travel vocabulary.</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.learnenglish.be/voc1_transport_study.htm\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"underline c1\">Means of transport.</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.speakenglish.co.uk/vocab/hotels_and_accommodation\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"underline c1\">Hotels and accommodation.</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.manythings.org/vocabulary/lists/2/words.php?f=countries_nationalities\" target=\"_blank\"><span class=\"underline c1\">Countries and nationalities.</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n"
                        }
                    ],
                    "sections": []
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "reference": {
                "value": "1392383"
            },
            "heading": {
                "type": "heading",
                "content": "Ready with this lesson?",
                "level": 1
            },
            "items": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.dentonisd.org/cms/lib/TX21000245/Centricity/Domain/5634/grades.jpg\" class=\"height-216-pixels width-176-pixels float-right\"/>The last 5 minutes of every lesson ends with this item. Remind your teacher when it is 5 minutes before!!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Have you filled in your workplan yet?</li>\n<li>Write down in your notebook what went right and what was difficult. Like this:\n<ul>\n<li>Date of the lesson and then something like:</li>\n<li>Right: I understand everything that was explained</li>\n<li>Difficult: I don't know everything there is to know about the Chromebook</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Did you learn new words? If so, write them in your notebook, to learn at home. Like this:\n<ul>\n<li>In the back of your notebook fold a page: left side = English; right side = Dutch</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Continue with WRTS or Duolingo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n"
                }
            ],
            "sections": []
        },
        {
            "reference": {
                "value": "1392385"
            },
            "heading": {
                "type": "heading",
